    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1308"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1308">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.77/132.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cumberland, Md.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have information which would be glad to have you confirm that there are as many
                    as two hundred and fifty American railway conductors and many locomotive
                    engineers and trainmen who have been thrown out of employment in Mexico and are
                    now refugees in El Paso and other border towns. If you can, verify this
                    information by telegraph to consuls at various places and to the Ambassador. I
                    should be glad if you would issue a statement by my direction inviting the
                    attention of railway presidents and managers to the presence <pb facs="1039"
                        n="923" xml:id="pg_923"/> of these skilled workmen with a view if possible
                    to securing employment for them and to save them from suffering.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
